+# Planner Portfolio - beyond-de-giorgi / run-005
+
+## Preserved Context
+
+- `beta = 4/3` is already sharp for the De Giorgi-Vasseur architecture. This run does not spend budget on De Giorgi tuning, pressure-`H^1` repackaging, or weakly disguised local-iteration variants.
+- The pressure-localization loophole was already killed inside the old coefficient-shrinkage architecture. Pressure can still appear here, but only through a genuinely different mechanism.
+- The neutral Eulerian geometry package was already killed. Any geometry branch carried forward here must make the package change itself explicit and auditable.
+- The fixed local-energy exact-rewrite audit already showed that prettier local identities are not enough. New chains must attach structure to a named bottleneck and a non-cosmetic gain.
+- Run-004 correctly elevated the critical-element route as the highest-upside branch, but that was a selector decision, not a proof that every alternative is dead. This new wide funnel keeps that route while reopening competition from more sharply specified NS-specific mechanisms.
+- Tao's averaged-NS obstruction remains the standing filter. In this portfolio it is embedded inside each chain rather than treated as a separate meta-chain.
+
+## Portfolio Summary
+
+### Chain 01 - Critical Element Program With Host-Space Freeze And Rigidity Admission
+
+Central premise: a compactness-rigidity route is live only if one host space, one critical object, and one admissible rigidity quantity survive theorem-by-theorem auditing.
+
+Why it belongs now: run-004 showed this remains the highest-ceiling route with the cleanest disciplined failure mode.
+
+### Chain 02 - Helical-Triad Symbol Route
+
+Central premise: if Tao-style averaging destroys something decisive, the most plausible place is the exact Leray-symbol and helical-triad geometry of the genuine NS quadratic interaction.
+
+Why it belongs now: this is the sharpest way to test "the specific algebraic form of `u . grad u`" without drifting back into cosmetic local rewrites.
+
+### Chain 03 - Tensor Stretching And Pressure-Hessian Route
+
+Central premise: the exact coupling among strain, vorticity, and the pressure Hessian may contain NS-specific structure that scalar norm methods erase but that still acts directly on stretching.
+
+Why it belongs now: it preserves the strongest pressure-adjacent live lead without reopening the dead coefficient-shrinkage branch.
+
+### Chain 04 - Local Beltrami Deficit To Geometric Criterion Bridge
+
+Central premise: exact Beltrami structure kills the Lamb-vector debt, and near-Beltrami vortex-core geometry may become useful only if it can be converted into a quantitative stretching or Constantin-Fefferman type criterion on intense-vorticity sets.
+
+Why it belongs now: this is the most concrete surviving geometry route after the neutral Eulerian package failed.
+
+## Major Differences Between Chains
+
+- Chain 01 is global and theorem-shaped. It starts from hypothetical blowup and tries to rule out a minimal counterexample.
+- Chain 02 is spectral and algebraic. It works at the exact triad-symbol level and asks for a localized cancellation or depletion mechanism there.
+- Chain 03 is tensorial and local-to-nonlocal. It targets `S omega . omega` and the pressure Hessian directly, with explicit nonlocal debt accounting.
+- Chain 04 is geometric and region-specific. It focuses on coherent high-vorticity structure, local Beltrami deficit, and whether that structure can survive transport and localization costs.
+
+## Portfolio Shape
+
+- Highest upside: Chain 01.
+- Most direct Tao-sensitive algebra route: Chain 02.
+- Best bridge from prior pressure findings to a new mechanism: Chain 03.
+- Most concrete geometry reboot: Chain 04.
+
+## Portfolio Discipline
+
+- Each chain must name one bottleneck quantity or theorem gap before optimism begins.
+- Each chain must state the first missing lemma if it survives.
+- Each chain may end negatively; useful obstruction is an intended output, not a failed run.
+- No standalone Tao-ranking chain is included. The Tao screen is now a required internal gate inside every candidate route.
+
+## Selector Guidance
+
+- If the next run wants the best expected value, start with Chain 01 or Chain 02.
+- If the next run wants the strongest pressure-adjacent test without reopening dead ground, start with Chain 03.
+- If the next run wants the cleanest geometry reboot under explicit package change, start with Chain 04.

